Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Symbolism=The Manifold Content of Symbols
By: St Thomas Aquinas
---
It is in no wise contrary to truth for intelligible things to be set
forth in Scripture under sensible figures, since it is not said for
the purpose of maintaining that intelligible things are sensible, but
in order that properties of intelligible things may be understood
according to similitude through sensible figures.
